Version 2.11:
- [+] 05 Sep 2007, Alien - Improvement (0022000): The module is adapted to commercial design schemas.
- [!] 30 Jul 2007, Alien - Bug (0024101): Related product with options bulk adding issue ...

Version 2.10:
- [!] 30 Jul 2007, Alien - Bug (0023746): The "Bulk Add to Cart" functionality in "Related Products" section didn't work correctly on static HTML-pages generated by the HTML Catalog module. Fixed.
- [+] 18 Jun 2007, Osipov - Improvement (0021831): The list of products in the "New Arrivals" section was populated in a non-optimal way. The optimization was performed.
- [!] 15 Jun 2007, Osipov - Bug (0021930): The link to a product on the "Notify me when..." dialogue was formed without information about the product category. As a result the navigation path in the product details dialogue didn't contain the product category name. Fixed.
- [!] 15 Jun 2007, Osipov - Bug (0021741): When the "Enable the functionality" option on the module configuration page was disabled, the inventory functionality did not work correctly. Fixed.
- [!] 08 May 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0017904): The module didn't take into account special behaviour of the PHP5-specific functions. Fixed.
- [+] 17 Apr 2007, Sheriff - Improvement (0017395): Now module templates are compatible with HTML 4.01 Transitional.

Version 2.9:
- [!] 02 Sep 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0011516): ProductAdviser did not take into account interaction with other modules during additional product data gathering, which sometimes caused strange behaviour. Fixed.

Version 2.8:
- [!] 27 Sep 2006, Osipov - Bug (0010154): Automatic HTML catalog rebuilding caused a crash. Fixed.
- [!] 30 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0010540): Some features in new versions of LiteCommerce (2.2.X) were supported incorrectly. Fixed.
- [+] 30 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0010154): Small refactoring of PHP code was performed to increase compatibility between ProductAdviser and HTMLCatalog modules (sometimes the catalog generation failed).
- [!] 11 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0010012): 'New Arrivals' and 'Recently viewed' lists sometimes had been populated incorrectly (occured when products were removed, but ProductAdviser did not handle that under certain conditions with some module combinations). Fixed.

Version 2.7:
- [!] 08 Aug 2006, Osipov - Bug (0009783): Product price notifications were not prepared automatically when admin updated products quantity data from a CSV file (when InventoryTracking module was enabled). Fixed.
- [!] 07 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0009853): The initial stock amount of a product was lost when customer placed a request for a notification about stock amount increase. Fixed.
- [!] 07 Aug 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0009783): Stock amount notifications were not prepared automatically when admin updated inventory data from a CSV file (when InventoryTracking module was enabled). Fixed.

Version 2.6:
- [!] 30 May 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0008873): The "New Arrivals" list was populated without taking into account the level of nesting of subcategories (when "Show category-specific new arrivals" option was turned on). Fixed.
- [!] 22 May 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0007772): The "multiple additions at once" functionality didn't take into account the presence of "Redirect customer to cart" option. Fixed.
- [!] 04 May 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0007398): The "Notify me" functionality on the "Product details" page of "out of stock" products, which was supposed to enable a customer to order a notification to be sent to himself when the product becomes "in stock", worked incorrectly with "out of stock" products that had product options and whose inventory was being tracked with product options. Fixed.
- [!] 30 Nov 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0005046): The "Notify me" functionality on the "Product details" page of "out of stock" products worked incorrectly (The page displayed as a result of using the "Notify me" link provided information not about the product being viewed currently, but about another "out of stock" product viewed previosly in the same session). Fixed.
- [!] 16 Nov 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0004789): 'New Arrivals' and 'Recently viewed' lists sometimes had been populated incorrectly (occured under certain conditions with some module settings & products number combinations). Fixed.

Version 2.5:
- [!] 31 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0004707): A product's relationships were not removed completely when a product was deleted. Fixed.
- [+] 28 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: "Show new arrivals only" option has been added to the product search form. Products with the "new arrival" status are marked with special icons in the search results.
- [!] 27 Oct 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0004671): The "as new" attribute was assigned incorrectly to newly added product (new product as assigned the 'forever new' attribute instead of the 'new for the default period' attribute). Fixed.

Version 2.4:
- [+] 20 Sep 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: Minor changes to the UI of the module's pages.
- [+] 16 Sep 2005, Sheriff - Improvement (0004106 ): The functionality of the 'New Arrivals' component has been expanded:
    * An option to show category-specific new arrivals has been introduced
    * The list of new arrivals can now be displayed in the Customer Zone either in a side-box or inside the main section

Version 2.3:
- [+] 17 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Improvement (0003675): Capability to add multiple related products to the shopping card at once has been introduced.

Version 2.2:
- [+] 02 Jun 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: "In-stock" and "price change" notifications can now be enabled independently.
- [+] 02 Jun 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: An additional functionality was added to make module fully compatible with the "FeaturedProducts" module.
- [+] 01 Jun 2005, Sheriff - Improvement: Support for new versions (2.10+) of the "HTMLCatalog" module was added.

